F-008 fixed and committed. Root cause: `_broad_question_mcq` was firing the "what are you trying to fix?" clarifier when users said "give me a checklist" because "checklist" wasn't in the skincare-specific regex, so the broad domain gate treated it as a vague intent. Fix adds an early-exit guard for explicit format keywords (`checklist`, `step-by-step`) before any domain check runs. VIS-05 now passes seeds 4 and 15. Next pass should verify F-009 and F-010 (which passed on seed 8 and may already be resolved by prior grammar work).
